Next, we initialize a memoization table (dp) and the prefix sum (useful for calculating the total sum of stones) in each language. We use three nested loops to account for all possible values of `l`, `i`, `j`, where `l` is the subarray length, and `ij` is the start and end indices. Then a fourth loop iterates through `m`, which is the number of piles to merge.

